<div data-role="collapsible" data-collapsed="true">
	<h3>What is this service?</h3>
	<p>Where’s My School Bus allows guardians of Boston Public School students to see on a map where their children’s school buses are in the city.</p>
</div>
<div data-role="collapsible" data-collapsed="true">
	<h3>Is the location of the bus on the map always accurate?</h3>
	<p>No.</p>
  <p>The location of the bus on the map comes from the school bus’s GPS (Global Positioning System) device.  For a number of reasons, that device can occasionally fail to work.  Consequently, the school bus will occasionally be in a different location than the one presented on the map.</p>
  <p>Occasionally, BPS Transportation must make bus substitutions due to repairs, route changes, or weather disruptions. If a different bus was substituted for your student’s normally assigned bus, you may not see the location of the bus your student is actually riding.</p>
  <p>If you need to confirm a bus location, you can all the BPS Transportation Hotline at (617) 635-9520.  The hotline is available Monday through Friday: 8:30 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.</p>
</div>
<div data-role="collapsible" data-collapsed="true">
  <h3>My student is supposed to be on a bus that hasn’t moved recently on the map. Why is that?</h3>
  <p>There are several reasons why a bus may not move on the map.</p>
  <p>Occasionally, BPS Transportation must make bus substitutions due to repairs, route changes, or weather disruptions. If a different bus was substituted for your student’s assigned bus, you may instead see the stationary location of your student’s normally assigned bus, rather that the bus he or she is actually riding.</p>
  <p>Additionally, sometimes the GPS (Global Positioning System) device on a bus can fail to work. If this occurs, the school bus may not appear on the map, or may appear in an inaccurate location. Rest assured that BPS Transportation is working as quickly as possible to restore GPS functionality.</p>
  <p>If you need to confirm a bus location, you can all the BPS Transportation Hotline at (617) 635-9520.  The hotline is available Monday through Friday: 8:30 a.m. - 5:00 p.m.</p>
</div>
<div data-role="collapsible" data-collapsed="true">
  <h3>What is the black line on the map behind the bus?</h3>
  <p>The black line behind a bus shows its previous location over the past 30 minutes. This line allows you to see a bus’s recent route and approximate rate of travel. If the bus has not moved in the last 30 minutes, you will not see a line on the map.</p>
</div>
